(122, 7, '#### Delegation of authority to another human rights agency

[2017, c.24, s.18](/en/nb/laws/astat/snb-2017-c-24/latest/snb-2017-c-24.html)

22.1(1)In the event of an actual or potential conflict of interest with respect to a complaint referred to the Commission, the Commission may, by written agreement entered into with another statutory human rights agency in Canada, delegate to that human rights agency the authority to exercise or perform some or all of the Commissions powers, duties and functions.

22.1(2)On the execution of an agreement referred to in subsection (1), the other human rights agency has, to the extent provided by the agreement, those powers, duties and functions of the Commission.

